  "text": "As with the analyses of SGA and preterm birth [CITATION_1] , the use of the color measurement appeared to add little to the study. For example, from the data provided in the study, we calculated an unadjusted odds ratio of 1.15 for \"all birth defects,\" comparing the chlorination proportions 0 and 100% without accounting for water color. This odds ratio was very close to the unadjusted (OR = 1.18) and adjusted (OR = 1.14) findings when both chlorination proportion and color level were taken into account.",
